ars in the Paris office of Bolles Brothers (1872-1875), he spent nearly fifty-five years with Kidder, Peabody & Company — the Boston banking firm whose name would later become synonymous with twentieth-century American investment banking. His December 1932 New York Times obituary called him a 'close friend of the late Gamaliel Bradford.'"},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"Williston Seminary then Williams College, 1871","body":"Educated at Westfield High School, then Williston Seminary at Easthampton MA, then Williams College in the Berkshires graduating 1871. Also treasurer of the Jessup & Lafflin Paper Company of Westfield alongside his banking work — the kind of manufacturing-finance combination characteristic of late 19th-c New England merchant capital."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Lost Ellen and two of three children young","body":"Married Ellen Jane Goodwin June 20, 1878 Pittsfield MA. She died July 31, 1901 Wellesley MA of nephritis age 44. Their daughter Sybil Hale died 1906 age 26; daughter Sarah Hale had died 1885 age 2 of uremic poisoning."}],"slug":"charles-hooker-1847-2"},"H05270":{"id":"H05270","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"generation_from_thomas":10,"is_easter_egg":false},"bio":{"display_name":"Sybil Hale Hooker","first_name":"Sybil","middle_name":"Hale","last_name":"Hooker","maiden_name":"Hooker","married_names":[]},"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1879,"month":11,"day":20,"city":"Pittsfield","county":"Berkshire","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1906,"month":3,"day":18,"notes":"Died age 26."},"burial":{"cemetery_name":"Pine Hill Cemetery","city":"Westfield","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"H04365","mother_id":"I01133"},"number_of_marriages":0,"marriages":[],"tags":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable